712074f-a.text:
West 33rd 3treet, south side, at Eleventh Avenue, showthe New York Central Railroad yards and the Eleventh Ave. ramp being carried across same. Fringing the southerly side of this extensive transportation locale, is the elevated roadbed that carries these trains southward to the St. John's Freight Depot, downtown. The buildings beyond are to the south of West 30th Street. The white utilitarian feature at the left is the new U. S. Parcel Post Bldg. on Ninth and Tenth Avenues. This replaced the old Milk Depot. On the riht margin appears a substantial part of the outstanding Starett-Lehigh Bldg. extending between
Eleventh and Thirteenth Avenue's.
August 24, 1940
No's. 1-2
P. L. Sperr
